reviewText: Raven & Saturn VS Ray Mysterio Jr. & Billy Kidman VS Dean Malenko & Chris Benoit: Best match of the card. Funny how WCW always put there best match of the card on first.Konnan VS Stevie Ray: Fast foward.Bam Bam Bigelow VS Brian Knobbs: A typical hardcore match with nothing really going on out of the ordinary.Rick Steiner VS Booker T: Despite Scott coming out, the match still went back and fourth for a few minutes. The ending was weak.Georgeous George VS Charles Robinson: Couldnt they have put a Flair-Savage match instead? A waste of time and money. Then again, the WCW superstars were probably wiping there butts with hundred dollar bills at the time.Scott Steiner VS Buff Bagwell: I cant belive I bought this PPV.Rowdy Roddy Piper VS Ric Flair: Oh thats why Flair didnt wrestle Savage earlier. A typical president vs president match that WCW did alot of.Sting VS Goldberg: This match was going so well. Then Hart interferes and its ruled a no contest. No wonder why fans left WCW in droves.Kevin Nash VS DDP: I actully enjoyed this match. I liked how Bischoff came down and said there must be a winner. Of course, Nash wins the belt.Overall, a pretty bad card with the first and last match being the only good matches of the night.

reviewText: All I can say is "How the hell did this get an average of *****?!?". Let's look at this PPV logically. The first match was just awesome! Kidman/Misterio v. Raven/Saturn v. Benoit/Malenko? Can you say "Five Stars", because I can say "Six!". But, if you have any regard for your sanity, stop the tape THERE! I mean they go from 6 of the best wrestlers in North America to Stevie Ray vs. Konnan (2 of the worst). And it's all down hill from there. The main event is Kevin Nash vs. Diamond Dallas Page, with Nash winning the title (because god knows that us wrestling fans wouldn't be able to survive without Diesel as champ!). This PPV took a HUGE step towards the end of WCW. So, I recommend everyone to watch the triple threat tag team opener, but PLEASE stop the tape there! You'll thank me later!
summary: The first match was awesome, but stop the tape THERE!

reviewText: Raven & Saturn vs. Ray Mysterio Jr. & Billy Kidman vs. Dean Malenko & Chris Benoit - Solid opening match, when you have guys that are good workers and actually know how to wrestle it makes out for a good match. 7/10Konnan vs. Stevie Ray - ummmmmmm I really didnt like this match..maybe because neither of these guys I have ever found that exciting so.....I would fast forward through this match.2/10Bam Bam Bigelow vs. Brian Knobbs - I didn't really expect much from this match but it was solid.....some cool and hardcore things happend. 6/10Rick Steiner vs. Booker T - Pretty good match. Booker should have won......wcw really liked having old champions I mean rick stiener has been wrestling since the 80's but a new Tv Champ.6/10Georgeous George vs. Charles Robinson -Very entertaining to me. CHarles robinson does an awsome ric flair impression. A funny match. 7/10Scott Steiner vs. Buff Bagwell - I didnt really care for this match. Boring. 3/10Rowdy Roddy Piper vs. Ric Flair - In their prime this would have made for a great match and it wasnt bad now but a little slower and a little more boring. 6/10Bill Goldberg vs. Sting -Pretty good match. Solid action through the whole fight but it would have been nice to have a real winner. 7/10Kevin Nash vs. DDP - Best match of the night with out a doubt. Both men were on top of their game and it wasn't boring and it wasnt slow a lot of near pinfalls and thank you eric bischoff for making th ematch go longer.9/10
